Q2/- Explain the difference between JPA and Hibernate?


JPA-
It is defined in javax.persistance package.
It uses JPQL as an object-oriented query Language to perform database operation.
It defines the management of relational data in the java application.

Hibernate-
It is defined org.hibernate package.
It uses HQL as an Object-oriented query Language to perform database operation.
It is a ORM tool which is used to save the state of java object into the database.


What are the advantages of using Hibernate over JDBC?

1.Hibernate Supports relationship like one to one ,many to may ,many to one.
2.It supports collection like List,Set,Map.
3.Hibernate Supports inheritence ,Associations,Collections etc.
4.Hibernate have translator that converts checked to unchecked.
